"Gainesville-Alachua County Where Nature And Culture Meets."@en

"Gainesville is the county seat and largest city in Alachua County in the U.S. state of Florida, and the principal city of the Gainesville, Florida Metropolitan Statistical Area (MSA). The population of Gainesville in the 2010 Census was 124,354. Gainesville is also the largest city in the region of North Central Florida. Gainesville is home to the University of Florida, the nation's seventh largest university campus by enrollment, as well as to Santa Fe College."@en
